Assuming the lens is at the focal length (72 meters), the magnification is: \[ m = \frac{72 \text{ meters}}{72 \text{ meters}} = 1 \] 5. **Calculate the diameter of the image**: - The diameter of the image is the magnification multiplied by the linear diameter of the object: \[ \text{Diameter of the image} = m \times \text{Linear diameter of the object} \approx 1 \times 2.006 \times 10^6 \text{ meters} \approx 2.006 \times 10^6 \text{ meters} \] 6. **Convert the linear diameter to centimeters**: \[ 2.006 \times 10^6 \text{ meters} = 2.006 \times 10^8 \text{ centimeters} \approx 1044 \text{ centimeters} \] Thus, the diameter of the image is \(\boxed{1044}\) centimeters.
